I think this plugin is required for other systems that might use something else instead of the "MMC". @Adriana Any thoughts?

There is a git issue already for this: https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-debug-collector/issues/17
we have agreed to send a note to community for now it is only for downstream, we will merge in upstream after community approval
LGTM

I'm ok with it being removed, an alternative would be to leave it but do not print the error message if the file doesn't exist.
The only system that currently supports the alternate environment is witherspoon, don't think this has being used for debug for the CI machines.
I think the alternative would be, copy file if exists else just ignore.

Agree - but the intent also is to optimize performance by removing a plugin which isn't going to be useful. Spoke to Adriana and she also indicated that there isn't a good reason why its useful even for Witherspoon.
It is not for 2 BMC systems, This is related to multiple flash  side supported boxes.
Considering backward compatibility , instead of printing errors , run the plugin only if the file is present.
